description: Let k = n-th number that is a possible digit-sum for a cube (A054966); sequence gives smallest cube with digit-sum k.
references: Amarnath Murthy, Fabricating a perfect cube with a given valid digit sum (to be published)
example: a(5) =2744, sum of digits = 17, the fifth term of A054966 (1,8,9,10,17,18...)
author: _Amarnath Murthy_, Apr 19 2001
